onInstall(bytes).details: This function is called by the smart account during installation of the module

params.data: arbitrary data that may be required on the module during `onInstall` initialization MUST revert on error (i.e. if module is already enabled)

validateUserOp((address,uint256,bytes,by.details: Validates a transaction on behalf of the account.         This function is intended to be called by the MSA during the ERC-4337 validaton phase         Note: solely relying on bytes32 hash and signature is not suffcient for some validation implementations (i.e. SessionKeys often need access to userOp.calldata)

params.userOp: The user operation to be validated. The userOp MUST NOT contain any metadata. The MSA MUST clean up the userOp before sending it to the validator.
params.userOpHash: The hash of the user operation to be validated
